  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: e7c51b06a4e84693a9494fdb5e5e0f30, type: 3}
  m_Name: DemonData_Sweenglyne
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: LSG::LSG.DemonData_Sweenglyne
  demonName: Sweenglyne
  canDateDemonMultipleTimes: 0
  introDialogue: 'You''re worried it didn''t work until a tidal wave of paperclips
    crashes through your door.  Office paper fountains out of the flow into a tsunami
    above you that hovers yet doesn''t crash down.  The top of a copy machine opens
    like a seashell revealing a figure with ink-black skin, a shirt of post-its,
    and a pencil skirt made of, well, pencils.  They take a sip from a toner cartridge
    while stapling you to the floor with their gaze.

    "You''re going to need
    to offer something better than the keys to the supply closet to keep my interest."'
  minimumPowerLevel: 1
  maximumPowerLevel: 10
  outcome: Sweenglyne clicks her tongue and shakes her head disapprovingly before
    melting away in a shower of toner ink. While cleaning the splatters from your
    desk, you realize your stapler, the charge cord for your phone, and half a sleeve
    of crackers are missing. But there is a roll of high-grade tape left in its place
    that crackles with a hellish energy. You're left with a great resource for your
    next summoning, but the irritating suspicion that your office supplies may be
    embezzled away by a demonic entity.
  boon: Gain 3 Tape
  bane: Unspent Tape is lost at the beginning of each new summoning round
  boonBaneDialogue: Sweenglyne's Curse has caused your extra Tape to disappear from
    your desk.
  dateOutcome: 'You''re surprised when they invite you to dinner at a normal, mortal
    restaurant.  You''re excited when they invite you to join them in a dimly lit
    back room of said restaurant.  You''re somewhat less surprised when they pulls
    a mask over your face and reveals this restaurant abutts an office supply store.


    You
    inscribe the wall-piercing rune and join them on their heist, shoving printer
    cartridges and shiny red staplers into the hellgate you draw in the middle of
    the store.  You do get a kiss before they vanish into the portal as the cops
    show up to the store.'
  demonSprite: {fileID: 6124846179822445239, guid: d487ff2fe7649253da5acef934c3f2b0, type: 3}
